CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 22 reads: "Crown Ebenezer's Popular Babies - Ebenezer Baptist Church, Pittsburgh, conducted a contest to select the most popular babies in church membership. Competition was keen and the winners were chosen by a very narrow margin.  Master Maurice Jackson, who won first prize, was not present when this picture was taken.  Mary Alice Cullins, winner of the second prize and her mother, Mrs. Paulean Cullins, are also shown.  Rev. T.J. King presented the prizes. - Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five women and four babies, including Paulean Cullins and daughter Mary Alice Cullins, seated in Ebenezer Baptist Church for the Most Popular Babies contest
